b'        INDIAN INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY MADRAS  Academic Section    Circular No.10/Acad/B2/JM2016&nbs;p;&nbsp; &nb;sp; &n;bsp;Dated: 15.03.2016    Dear Students/Scholars,    Sub:  Makeup examination  adherence of rules  &nb;sp;&nb;sp;&nb;sp;    Students who missed the Quizzes / Midsemester / End Semester examinations on valid medical reasons etc. should submit an application request through workflow   (using Roll No and Password) within 10 days from the date of examination and report to the course teacher/coordinator.  Go through the attached help document which provides detailed procedure and necessary screenshots.  The concerned faculty are requested to give the approval for the makeup online application through   with ADS userid/password Rules Relating To Production Of Medical Certificate Along With MakeUp Application Form Are As Follows (effective from July 2003 semester)  Students residing in the hostels should produce a Medical Certificate issued by the Chief Medical Officer of IIT Madras that he/she was admitted in the Hospital during the period of missed Quiz(zes) / Midsemester / End Semester examination. Students residing in the Hostels and taking medical consultation with outside Doctors are required to obtain written permission from the Chief Medical Officer, Institute Hospital, IIT Madras,  before they proceed for consultation, or within three days of the date of joining after illness.  Otherwise, the sick student has to visit one of those hospitals recognized under the Mediclaim Insurance Scheme. <li Students staying outside the campus permanently or temporarily have to produce medical certificate for inpatient treatment from the Institute Hospital or from any of the approved hospitals under the Mediclaim Insurance Scheme and the same be duly endorsed by the parent/guardian.     Application forms received for make up examination after the due date will not be considered.   Sd/   Deputy Registrar (Courses)   To    All students  through  students@list.iitm.ac.in       Copy to:    1. All Heads of the Department & HoD&#'

